## If work landed on the wrong rail

Misplaced feature commits on `distro/nix` should move to `main`; do not merge
`distro/nix` wholesale into `main`, because that mixes the branch roles. Rebase
or cherry-pick only the misplaced commits:

```sh
git fetch github upstream
base=$(git merge-base github/main github/distro/nix)
git switch -C reconcile/distro-nix-misplaced github/distro/nix
git rebase --onto github/main "$base"
git switch main
git merge --ff-only reconcile/distro-nix-misplaced
git push github main
```

Resetting the remote `distro/nix` rail after that requires an intentional
`--force-with-lease` maintenance push. Keep a backup ref first and do not do it
casually.

Use short-lived topic branches for work in progress:
